## Conventions

- New decisions append at top (most recent first) for `tracking/decisions.md`; long-form mirrors in `docs/decisions/` keep their own files.
- Every ADR MUST have ≥3 alternatives with calibrated fit %.
- Every ADR MUST cite its evidence (EU AI Act article, Anthropic doc, internal artifact, external research).
- Superseding ADRs link from the old entry: `Status: superseded by ADR-NNN`.
- Self-confidence < 70% on any ADR triggers HITL review at the next session checkpoint (per P2).
- Forbidden tokens in rationale: "best", "always", "guaranteed", "certain". Use calibrated language.

